classInfo.name: Matt Kraatz
classInfo.aboutMe: Part genre-agnostic music enthusiast, part business intelligence nerd, I left a successful career in sales operations to join NSS and haven't looked back since.

classInfo.name: Garrett Vangilder
classInfo.aboutMe: I love learning about how technology is used to make the world a better place. In my spare time I enjoy watching football, eating Indian food, and losing at boardgames.

classInfo.name: Elizabeth Sanger
classInfo.aboutMe: Former English professor and forever feline apologist, I'm obsessed by the intersection between language and meaning and passionate about development as a means to strengthen communities.

classInfo.name: Matt Hamil
classInfo.aboutMe: Loose-leaf tea connoisseur, purveyor of Bash scripts to automate workflow. I love learning about UX design and machine learning. I live for helping other newer developers experience those "Ahah!" moments.

classInfo.name: Casey Reed
classInfo.aboutMe: Nashville-based developer with an eye for UI/UX, clean code, whiteboard teaching, and rare vinyl records from the 1980s.

classInfo.name: Charles (Jamie) Duke
classInfo.aboutMe: Arizona transplant with a love for all things green and arboreal. Formerly employed by a home healthcare company, I came to NSS to magnify my interests in crafting technology.

classInfo.name: Chris Smalley
classInfo.aboutMe: Creative yet analytical developer with an MBA. Besides long walks on the beach and candlelit dinners, I enjoy UI/UX design, scholarly research, and actually like CSS.

classInfo.name: Thomas (Thom) Shavor
classInfo.aboutMe: Health care epidemiologist and NOLA transplant who enjoys experiencing the world through music and photography.  Love understanding how stuff works, and try to learn something new each day

classInfo.name: David Yunker
classInfo.aboutMe: I’m a news junkie and former journalist who’s driven to always find the answer and to solve problems. In my spare time, I'm driven to find quality beer, quality shows and quality time with my cats.

classInfo.name: Debbie Bourne
classInfo.aboutMe: With a background in Psychology and historic site administration, I'm fascinated by how technology improves our lives. I want to build apps that help us be better people.

classInfo.name: Meg Ducharme
classInfo.aboutMe: Software has played an instrumental role in helping me start a company, teach, manage construction projects, and stay in touch with friends. With these experiences, coupled with my new understanding of front & back end technologies, I’m excited to empower others through software!

classInfo.name: Zack Repass
classInfo.aboutMe: A native Nashvillian with a big picture mindset excited by new ideas and the possibilities presented to us by new tools and technologies. With a desire to build people up, I am excited to join an industry that can inspire people through technology to be their best self.

classInfo.name: Anulfo Ordaz
classInfo.aboutMe: I'm former Venezuelan surgeon with a strong inclination for Software Development. Service to others is the only way to improve society, being true to that ideal is my motivation

classInfo.name: Edgar Barajas
classInfo.aboutMe: Approaching life with a student mentality with the aspiration of one day becoming the teacher has helped me become the professional I am today. Consider myself a well rounded individual who can hold my own in any environment I am thrown into ranging from a room full of hyperactive 5 year olds to black tie events. Looking forward to hearing from you!

classInfo.name: Yonatan Molla
classInfo.aboutMe: A former Agro-Mechanization Engineer becoming a Software Developer Excited by new technologies.
